HEMORRHAGIC FEVER, EBOLA SUSPECTED - CONGO, DEM. REP. (03)
*********************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.healthnet.org/programs/promed.html>
See Also
Hemorrhagic fever, Ebola suspected - Congo, Dem. Rep. (02) 990502033738
Hemorrhagic fever, Ebola suspected - Congo, Dem. Rep. 990430222141
[1
Date: Mon, 03 May 1999 18:41:23 -0400
From: Thomas James Allen <tjallen@pipeline.com>
Source: Pan African News Agency, 2 May 1999 [edited

An epidemic of Ebola fever has killed 58 people in Watsa, in the eastern province of the
Democratic Republic of Congo, Health Minister Mashako Mamba Saturday announced in Kinshasa.
He said the victims were among the 70 Ebola patients reported in the region, and added that the
epicentre of the oubreak was Faradja, 60 km from the Sundanese border.
The disease is now spreading to the localities of Durba and Watsa - respectively 90 km and 120 km
to the south - and Isiro, more than 200 km southwest of Kinshasa, Mamba said.
He also said that two doctors were handling the patients in Watsa while other medical teams and
local representatives of the WHO and the French charity, Medecins Sans Frontieres were assigned
in the affected regions which are under the control of rebels loyal to the Congolese Democratic
Rally, fighting the government since 2 Aug 1998.
He said Ebola control specialists, who assisted in curbing the epidemics in 1987 and 1995 in
Yambuku and Kikwit, are expected soon in the affected areas.

